org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.traffico

Class TrafficoSign

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openstreetmap.josm.plugins.mapillary.traffico.TrafficoSign

  • public final class TrafficoSign
extends java.lang.Object

    Representation of a traffico sign, which consists of a country code, a unique name and the individual layers of the sign.

    You can obtain a TrafficoSign via getSign(String, String). The first call to that method reads all sign definition for the queried country from disk and holds them in memory for future access.

    You can rely on the fact, that two instances of TrafficoSign with same getName() and same getCountry() that were obtained via getSign(String, String) will return true when compared with ==

      • getSign

        public static TrafficoSign getSign(java.lang.String country,
                                   java.lang.String signName)

        Returns the sign associated with the given country and name or null if no such sign is available.

        If you obtain two instances of TrafficoSign with this method that have the same country and name, you can safely assume that a comparison of both objects with == will result in true.

        Parameters:
        country - the country to which the sign belongs
        signName - the name of the sign (unique in a country)
        Returns:
        the requested sign or null if this sign is unavailable
